5:
Snow, lights, smiles... It's beginning to
look a lot like the holidays!
9:
Did you know they're decorating
that tree in the plaza today? And I'm
here to help!
17:
No duh, Baloosh! Wouldn't be any
fun without you!
20:
Hey, Aureo! Have you seen a star
floating around?
21:
We've been looking for hours, but it's
like it vanished into thin air.

I swear it was here yesterday...
23:
Wait, we've lost our tree-topper?!
That can't be good.
26:
It was in a box like this one. Let us
know if you find it, okay, Aureo?
29:
Huh? I feel like I've seen this box
before... But where...
33:
OH!

You guys sent out a delivery
yesterday, right? To the
Kaleidoscope! There was a box just
like this jumbled in.
36:
*gasp* YOU'RE RIGHT! I'm so sorry,
everyone. I must've gotten the
packages mixed up.
42: It was, uh... Oh! Johnny's party!
46:
Let me go find them real quick!
Pretty sure it's still too early in the
morning for them to have gone
questing.
50: A-Aureo! There's a bit of a problem...
59:
Could something have befallen
them in the Kaleidoscope?
62:
We've got to look for them. They
might need help.
65: Aureo and Baloosh are on the case!
76:
There is no sign of them. Perhaps
they ventured farther in...
79:
Aureo, Baloosh. Any monsters up
ahead are gonna be on a different
level. Think you can handle it?
84:
You bet! Baloosh and I have learned
a lot from our adventures.
90:
You know, more and more
adventurers have been asking us to
make deliveries for them.
94:
It makes me happy 'cause I love my
job! My favorite part is when you
hand over the package and get a
big "thank you" in return!
98:
Gratitude is one of the most
valuable gifts in this world.
102:
You can say that—
...Huh? What is it, Baloosh?
119:
Baloosh! Aureo! Are we glad to see
you!
125:
Yeah, now that you're here!

But, come to think of it... why ARE you
here?
127:
We heard you never returned from
your quest. And... we're searching for
a star.
131:
You remember the delivery I made
yesterday? Was there a star mixed
in there, by any chance?
133: Oh... Oh yeah! You talking about this?
140:
We're the ones that should be
thanking you. We'd run clean out of
pots and were THIS CLOSE to giving
up the ghost.
142:
Yeah. You saved our lives, little
porter.
145:
I can see why Aureo loves his job
now. It's so much more than
delivering packages.
156:
Aureo! I knew you'd pull through,
little fella! Thanks!
158:
Well! Soon as that star's on top of
the tree, the holidays will be officially
here!
169:
You want to put the star on the tree,
don't you?
176:
Ahaha! All right then. Usually, putting
on the star's my job, but I think
Aureo's proven himself more than
worthy of the honor.
180:
Wait, really?

Yay! We'll do it together, Baloosh!
You ready?
